  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Facility for Refugees in Turkey</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">As part of the EU-Turkey cooperation on migration management EU and its Member States have established a Facility for Refugees in Turkey. The aim of the support is to respond to the immediate humanitarian and development needs of Syrian refugees in Turkey 
by delivering food education and health services. As a result the capacity of Turkey to receive and host refugees is enhanced and the living conditions of Syrian refugees in Turkey are improved incl. access to education and health services. The total fundi
ng of the facility is 3 billion euros of which 1 billion euros comes from EU budget and 2 billion euros from the budgets of the Member States. As an EU Member State Finland is obliged to participate in the funding with a share of 284 million euros in the y
ears 2016-2019.</narrative>
  </description>
